{"TopicId":171663,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"How to write a mod","CreatedByName":"Xylenox","CreatedById":185452,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-04T16:52:11Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Xylenox","CreatedById":185452,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-04T16:52:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHello,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan someone please explain the basics on how to write a mod and/or link a tutorial? I am kind of experienced in programming.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HebaruSan","CreatedById":156657,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-04T17:18:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s a subforum dedicated to it:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/forum/36-add-on-development/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Ehttps://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/forum/36-add-on-development/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAssuming you want to write a plugin rather than make parts, this is a good place to start:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed6281162586\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/153765-getting-started-the-basics-of-writing-a-plug-in/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:211px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rodhern","CreatedById":144074,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-04T17:57:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe Diazo link is indeed a good one. If I may add one comment though. In general C# is the best/safe bet, especially if you already know C#, but you don\u0027t have to choose C#;\u00A0most dotnet languages will do.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sarbian","CreatedById":57146,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-05T10:21:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223310048\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171663\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520186224\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022144074\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Rodhern\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 hours ago, Rodhern said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe Diazo link is indeed a good one. If I may add one comment though. In general C# is the best/safe bet, especially if you already know C#, but you don\u0027t have to choose C#;\u00A0most dotnet languages will do.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is true but 99% of the ressource you ll find on KSP modding (and Unity to a lesser degree) use\u00A0C#\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HebaruSan","CreatedById":156657,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-05T11:57:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223310534\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171663\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520245288\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257146\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sarbian\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, sarbian said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is true but 99% of the ressource you ll find on KSP modding (and Unity to a lesser degree) use\u00A0C#\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd if you need help modding Kerbal in VB.NET or F#, you\u0027ll have a harder time than with C#.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}